com.vanillasource.jaywire.proxy

Interface Proxy<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SupplierProxy
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Proxy<T>
    Proxies calls to an unerlying object.

    • Method Detail

      • call

        <R> R call(Function<T,R> body)
        Call object inside this proxy. The object will be supplied to the function given.

      • onAround

        default Proxy<T> onAround(BiConsumer<T,Runnable> around)
        Execute additional logic around the call. To execute the body supplied by user, call the received runnable. If the runnable is not called in the 'around' handler, null will be returned.
        Returns:
        A proxy that will execute the supplied 'around' handler.
